(132, 1, '2017-07-14 23:25:14', '2017-07-14 23:25:14', '[vc_row type=\"full_width_background\" full_screen_row_position=\"middle\" bg_color=\"#f1fbff\" scene_position=\"center\" text_color=\"dark\" text_align=\"left\" top_padding=\"100\" bottom_padding=\"100\" overlay_strength=\"0.3\"][vc_column column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" width=\"1/1\" tablet_text_alignment=\"default\" phone_text_alignment=\"default\"][vc_row_inner text_align=\"left\"][vc_column_inner column_padding=\"padding-3-percent\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" centered_text=\"true\" width=\"1/6\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner column_padding=\"padding-3-percent\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" width=\"2/3\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h1 class=\"p1\" style=\"color: #1e9af4; text-align: center;\">The VisitDays Story</h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" width=\"1/6\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row type=\"full_width_background\" full_screen_row_position=\"middle\" bg_image=\"138\" bg_position=\"center center\" bg_repeat=\"no-repeat\" scene_position=\"center\" text_color=\"dark\" text_align=\"left\" id=\"founder\" overlay_strength=\"0.3\"][vc_column column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" width=\"1/1\" tablet_text_alignment=\"default\" phone_text_alignment=\"default\"][image_with_animation image_url=\"133\" alignment=\"center\" animation=\"Fade In\" box_shadow=\"none\" max_width=\"100%\"][divider line_type=\"No Line\" custom_height=\"30\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h4 class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"s1\">Sujoy Roy | Founder &amp; CEO</span></h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row type=\"full_width_background\" full_screen_row_position=\"middle\" bg_color=\"#ffffff\" scene_position=\"center\" text_color=\"dark\" text_align=\"left\" top_padding=\"100\" bottom_padding=\"100\" overlay_strength=\"0.3\"][vc_column column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" width=\"1/6\" tablet_text_alignment=\"default\" phone_text_alignment=\"default\"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" width=\"2/3\" tablet_text_alignment=\"default\" phone_text_alignment=\"default\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p class=\"p1\">The genesis of VisitDays came almost 3½ years ago as I sat at my parents’ kitchen table in Connecticut. At the time, I was working for publicly traded consulting firm. I remember that dinner fondly because it would change the trajectory of the next few years of my life.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Some context to set the stage for this dramatic transition: both my parents are professors — my dad, a professor of business; my mom, a professor of psychology. I asked them how things were going at their respective institutions. The story that my father told in response would become the thesis of VisitDays.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">My dad was invited by the admissions office at his institution to be the primary guest speaker at its annual open house. An expected 900 attendees were registered to visit, and the admissions office was working around the clock to make the event a success. The institution depended heavily on this particular event for recruiting students.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">A few weeks before the open house, he had asked the admissions office to give him some stats on who will be arriving to the open house. The office had all the tools at its disposal, including a world premier CRM, but my father never got a report that would have allowed him to make his talk relevant to the audience. That\'s where things got interesting. ...</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">A few days passed and he asked again. Again, nothing came through. Keep in mind that the admissions office had been able to drum up hundreds of registrants, so it had done all the hard stuff. Generating interest and getting the students there was 90 percent of the battle. But when it came to data, it was hard to get. The CRM was not easy to navigate, and certainly not easy to understand for every single member of the admission staff. It simply was not intuitive or easy.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Going into the open house, my dad decided to stick to what he knew best — the business school. He started to talk about the business school and how amazing it was. As he stood before the large audience, he very quickly realized something: Not a single person cared. Every face in that room was blank. No one cared, and he knew it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">So he decided to do something that would make every admissions officer cringe. He stopped midway through the presentation. He was determined to get to the bottom of what was going on. So he asked everyone, \"Raise your hand if you are interested in the School of Business.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">No one raised a hand.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">He suddenly realized that no one knew who he was and that he didn\'t know them.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Back at the dinner table, he looked at me and said, \"Someone really should solve this problem.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Two weeks later, I quit my job and began building VisitDays.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Now, more than 3½ years later, we are in dozens of undergraduate and graduate programs. More than 250,000 students have scheduled daily tours, open houses, admitted student days and one-on-one meetings, and institutions across the country are accessing data in ways they never imagined doing previously.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Institutions that use VisitDays are motivated by data and unhinged by change. They understand that the world is changing and to have a data driven strategy is table stakes. Each of our customers have seen anywhere between a 15-40% increase in show up rates. If you estimate a 70% of students that visit end up yielding, the math speaks for itself.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">I didn’t expect to throw myself into higher education, but from what I hear from our customers, nobody does. Higher education has a way to pull you in.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Sujoy Roy</h5>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" width=\"1/6\" tablet_text_alignment=\"default\" phone_text_alignment=\"default\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'About Us', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'about-us', '', '', '2017-07-14 23:27:22', '2017-07-14 23:27:22', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?page_id=132', 0, 'page', '', 0),
